er with a length of 13 cm (5.1 in). The upperparts are a range of shades of blue with white lores and a prominent white patch on each side of the neck. The underparts are white with an azure-blue breast-band. The bill is blackish and the legs are dark brown. The female has duller and slightly greenish plumage and a narrower breast band. Distribution and habitat The cerulean kingfisher is native to Sumatra, Java, the Kangean Islands, Bali, Lombok and Sumbawa, all in Indonesia. It is a resident species that inhabits low-lying areas near streams, canals, flooded paddy-fields and tidal estuaries. References", "shortSummary": "The cerulean kingfisher (Alcedo coerulescens) is a kingfisher in the subfamily Alcedininae which is native to parts of Indonesia. With an o…", "locations": ["路易·皮埃尔·维埃约", "翠鸟亚科", "蘇門答臘島", "爪哇岛", "康厄安群島", "巴厘省", "龙目岛", "松巴哇島"], "habitats": ["海岸湿地", "河口"], "lat": -5.0, "lng": 120.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/Cerulean_Kingfisher_0A2A1617.jpg/960px-Cerulean_Kingfisher_0A2A1617.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-alcedo", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-alcedo-coerulescens", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-alcedo", "species": "taxonomy-species-alcedo-coerulescens"}, "expandable": true, "x": 178.07, "y": -136.38, "z": -709.32}], "links": [{"key": "bird-cerulean-kingfisher-6f622f1d__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-alcedo-coerulescens", "source": "bird-cerulean-kingfisher-6f622f1d", "target": "taxonomy-species-alcedo-coerulescens", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-alcedo-coerulescens__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-alcedo", "source": "taxonomy-species-alcedo-coerulescens", "target": "taxonomy-genus-